description:
V1.1.3 - Added parking garage and lot searches and fixed photo issues with WebOS 1.4.
V1.1.2 - Added ability to delete saved GPS and photo information
V1.1.1 - Added ability to take photos and write notes 
V1.1.0 - Initial submission 
Where My Car At is a Palm WebOS application that helps the user
remember parking locations using GPS, photo and notes entered by the
user. It also includes a parking meter feature that optionally notifies
the user of an expiring meter. Once a parking location has been
remembered, the user can use Google Maps to view it on the map or to see
the saved photo and navigate back to the vehicle. Also, the user can
notify others via email all saved location, photo, meter and notes
information.  When a location or photo is no longer needed, it can be deleted 
separately.  For users looking for parking garages and lots, search with either 
the current GPS location or any address.  I will be continuing to update the 
application in future releases with new features and popular requests from users.
